National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Final Report
Location: GLENDALE, AZ
Accident Number: LAX82DA112
Date & Time: 03/01/1982, 1640 MST
Registration: N2524U
Aircraft: PIPER PA-28-161
Aircraft Damage: Substantial
Defining Event:
Injuries: 2 None
Flight Conducted Under: Part 91: General Aviation - Business
 Analysis WHILE TAXIING FOR TAKEOFF, THE RIGHT WING OF THE AIRCRAFT COLLIDED WITH A SIGN THAT WAS LOCATED BESIDE THE TAXIWAY.
Probable Cause and Findings The National Transportation Safety Board determines the probable cause(s) of this accident to be: Findings Occurrence #1: ON GROUND/WATER COLLISION WITH OBJECT Phase of Operation: TAXI - TO TAKEOFF Findings 1.
(F) OBJECT 2.
(C) CLEARANCE - MISJUDGED - PILOT IN COMMAND Factual Information Pilot Information Certificate: Private Age: 32, Male Airplane Rating(s): Single-engine Land Seat Occupied: Unknown Other Aircraft Rating(s): Glider Restraint Used: Instrument Rating(s): None Second Pilot Present: Instructor Rating(s): None Toxicology Performed: Medical Certification: Class 3 Valid Medical--no waivers/lim.
